<item>
            <title>[BEAM-3016] BeamFnLoggingClient shutdown stability</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-3016</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The BeamFnLoggingClient has a race condition where it may not shutdown appropriately if the channel has an error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This occurs because the stream observer created by the StreamObserverFactory may block indefinitely if the DirectStreamObserver is used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
